    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-09-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="434"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <head>434. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_KJF2" type="from"
                        >Kennedy</persName> to Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1"
                        type="to">McNamara</persName>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d434fn0">Source: Washington National Records
                        Center, RG 330, <gloss target="#t_OASD1">OASD</gloss> (C) A Files: <gloss
                            target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> 71 A 2896, Cuba 381, 22 Oct-27 Oct 1962.
                        Top Secret. A stamped note on the source text indicates <persName
                            corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName> saw the memorandum.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-09-21">September 21, 1962</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At the meeting with you and the Joint Chiefs of Staff on Friday, 14
                        September,<note n="1" xml:id="d434fn1">The President held an off-the-record
                        meeting with the Joint Chiefs and <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">McGeorge
                            Bundy</persName> at 11:40 a.m. on September 14. (<persName
                            corresp="#p_KJF2">Kennedy</persName> Library, Presidentʼs Appointment
                        Book)</note> there seemed to be lack of unanimity between General LeMay and
                        <persName corresp="#p_AGWJ1">Admiral Anderson</persName> as to losses our
                    aircraft would incur in attacking an SA2 missile site.</p>
                <p>Would it be useful to build a model of such a site for exercises to be observed
                    by an objective and disinterested party? Judgement as to losses to be incurred
                    should include those that would result from the addition of anti-aircraft guns
                    to protect the site. If you believe such a program would be useful, would you
                    provide me with an estimate as to its cost.</p>
                <p>Would you assure that contingency plans with relation to Cuba are kept
                    up-to-date, taking into account the additions to their armaments resulting from
                    the continuous influx of Soviet equipment and technicians.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KJF2">
                            <hi rend="strong">John Kennedy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
